      • checkTwoArgumentStringLiterals

        public static void checkTwoArgumentStringLiterals(String label,
                                                  NodeValue arg1,
                                                  NodeValue arg2)
        Check for string operations with primary first arg and second second arg (e.g. CONTAINS). The arguments are not used in the same way and the check operation is not symmetric.
      • "abc"@en is compatible with "abc"
      • "abc" is NOT compatible with "abc"@en
